The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning to generate programs for diverse scenes conditioned on symbolic instructions. This involves the use of image recognition and 3D modeling, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of reinforcement learning and adversarial learning also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of generating diverse outputs, which could be considered a problem in control systems (cs.SY).
